/phan/phan-14716/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14716/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14716/canvas/1/9aa108bd-9b62-4b49-acfd-dca57eb073bf","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-02T19:51:54.444Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The colors and handcrafted qualities of the revelers’ costumes clash with Reynolds’s and Alma’s more fashionable outfits. These details are significant for several reasons. Reynolds and Alma, no less than the partygoers, also play roles throughout the film in their attempts to gain the upper hand in their relationships. Likewise, the film emphasizes the performativity and theatricality of the London haute couture scene.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14716/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:964.6621218152864,36.31618232484084,477.9884056528663,1008.9261544585986"}}}]}]}]}